cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the transmission of confidential messages over a wireless broadcast channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of cooperative jamming and lattice alignment techniques suggests a focus on networked information systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the use of i.i.d. coding and the asymmetric compute-and-forward decoding strategy suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
